subSubSection.paragraph:
Head.
Subapical antennal flagellomeres longer than wide and not moniliform, flagellomeres normally setose except aberrant, smooth and shiny apical one, first flagellomere 1.1 × as long as second flagellomere, penultimate and apical flagellomeres (15th and 16th) 1.1 and 2.2 × as long as their width, respectively (
Fig. 7B
). Face without medio-longitudinal ridge and/or prominence (
Fig. 7D
).

Metasoma.
T1 hardly narrowed posteriorly. T1 largely parallel-sided, largely strongly rugose, but posteriorly smooth and shiny. T2 transversely narrowed, rectangular, laterally with a very weak sloping sides, apically completely straight and medium-sized, T2 largely with strong rugae. T3 longer than T2 and smooth (
Figs 8C–8D
). Ovipositor sheath comparatively wide basally and slightly broadening toward apex, smooth and with long whitish setae, especially apically, setose part 0.9 × as long as metatibia (
Fig. 8E
).

General distribution (Fig. 11D): Holarctic: Austria , Bulgaria , Canada ( Newfoundland and Labrador , Nova Scotia ,
Prince Edward Island
), France , Germany , Greece , Hungary , Iran , Israel ( new record ), Poland , Romania , Russia ( Sakhalin Oblast , Saratov Oblast ), Slovakia , Spain ( new record ), Switzerland , United Kingdom .
